text: Jorma Vilho Paavali Kinnunen (15 December 1941 â€“ 25 July 2019) was a Finnish athlete. He competed mainly in the javelin throw. He was born in Pihtipudas. He competed for Finland in the 1968 Summer Olympics held in Mexico City where he won the silver medal. Kinnunen died after a long illness on 25 July 2019, aged 77. ==References== Category:1941 births Category:2019 deaths Category:Finnish athletes Category:Olympic silver medalists for Finland Category:Javelin throwers
